      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my realtor just mentioned something about needing an escrow account for this house i'm looking at in toronto. i've never bought a place before so i'm kinda lost. can u explain what escrow actually is and why it's even used in the closing process?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Sure, I can help with that! Escrow is a financial arrangement where a third party holds and regulates the payment of the funds required for two parties involved in a given transaction. In the context of buying a house, the escrow account ensures that the buyer's funds and the seller's property are protected until all the terms of the sale are met. It's a way to make sure that neither party gets their money or property before everything is properly arranged and agreed upon. This helps prevent any potential disputes and ensures a smooth closing process. It's a good idea to have an escrow account, especially if you're a first-time homebuyer, as it adds a layer of security and peace of mind to the transaction.",
